backend:
    godown:
        add new godown
        edit existing godown
        get all godowns of the current user
        on clicking godown it should display what products it has
    godown rentals:
        search for others godowns to send a rent request
        accept/reject the request
    trade:
    user A creates a trade by selecting user B.
    once trade is created he will add products by selecting products from godown. if the trade is successful then those products will be removed from that godown.
    user B can accept of reject the trade.
    if user B accepts then he need to choose his godowns to which he will store the products.
        create trade-> gets user A and user B user_id and trade type and then adds it to table by keeping created as a default status.
        add items-> it will get trade id, product id, quantity, price and from godownId from frontend and inserts into the trade item table.
        send req-> after adding all the items userA clicks send button to send the request. Now the status changes from created to pending.
        getreceivedTradesbyuserId-> user B will get all the trades in which he is counterparty.
        accept/reject trade-> here the service will be same but it will call different model based on th response.
        if he rejects then status will be changed to rejected and nothing changes, if he accepts then from user A we need to removw those products and add them into user B's godown, user B's godowns will be selected by him only.
        now trade is completed.


